---
By: Ralph W. Trine
Locus:
  Page: 396
  Verse: 7
Tags:
  - Relationship
---
Many people are greatly enslaved by what we term ties of relationship. It
is well, however, for us to remember that our true relatives are not
necessarily those who are connected with us by ties of blood. Our truest
relatives are those who are nearest akin to us in mind, in soul, in spirit.
